              ]
            }
          ],
          "FACILITY": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "facility": [
                  "ISOCY"
                ],
                "institute": "2SF ABA"
              },
              "free_text": [
                " the external beam of the Abo Akademi",
                "University 103 cm isochronous variable-energy AVF",
                "cyclotron (MGC-20)."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Nine Hf-foils, nominal thickness 8 mum, purity 97.0%,",
                "interleaved with Al, 40 and 80 mum and high-purity Cu",
                "monitor foils, 7 mum."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "ACTIV",
                "STTA",
                "EXTB",
                "GSPEC",
                "BCINT"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                "",
                "After the irradiation, the Hf foils were analysed with",
                "a gamma spectrometer. Two sets of measurements were",
                "done, the first starting after about 24 h decay time,",
                "the second after about 3 weeks decay time. The 3-week",
                "decay time for the determination of 177Lu was needed",
                "because of interfering gamma lines from 177Ta and high",
                "background produced by other, short-living Ta isotopes."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "HPGE"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The HPGe detector (Canberra GAMMA-X with",
                "20.7% relative efficiency) used for determining the",
                "activity was calibrated using 57Co, 60Co, 137Cs and",
                "152Eu point sources."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ERR-ANALYS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "heading": "ERR-T",
                "minimum_value": null,
                "maximum_value": null,
                "correlation_property": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " The main contribution to the uncertainty",
                " (one standard deviation) in the cross-section values",
                "comes from the following sources:"
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "heading": "ERR-1",
                "minimum_value": 3.0,
                "maximum_value": 8.0,
                "correlation_property": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                ". HPGe efficiency calibration 3-8%,",
                "depending on the energy and the least-squares nuclide",
                "fit."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "heading": "ERR-2",
                "minimum_value": null,
                "maximum_value": null,
                "correlation_property": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                ".Error in the beam intensity is 5%."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "heading": "ERR-3",
                "minimum_value": null,
                "maximum_value": null,
                "correlation_property": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                ".Error in the number of target atoms in the beam",
                "is 5%."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "heading": "ERR-4",
                "minimum_value": null,
                "maximum_value": null,
                "correlation_property": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                ".Error in  the peak-area fitting with",
                "additional exponential tails and background fitted to",
                "individual peaks is 1%.",
                "UniSAMPO- Shaman analysis software given the activity",
                "of the nuclide and associated uncertainty at the end of",
                "the irradiation. This reported uncertainty includes the",
                "uncertainties of the efficiency calibration, peak-area",
                "fitting, the decay data and the half-life. Therefore,",
                "the estimated uncertainty of the cross-section values",
                "was obtained by adding quadratically the activity",
                "uncertainty from UniSAMPO-Shaman to the beam-intensity",
                "and target-thickness uncertainties."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "heading": "EN-ERR",
                "minimum_value": null,
                "maximum_value": null,
                "correlation_property": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                ".Uncertainty in the energy is reported by",
                "authors in table 1-The beam-energy uncertainty is",
                "estimated to be +-300 keV in the first foils and",
                "increase to +-750 keV in the last foil.This uncertainty",
                "includes the energy uncertainty of the extracted beam,",
                "the effect of the non-uniform foil thicknesses as well",
                "as uncertainties in the mean mass thicknesses and the",
                "initial beam-energy spread."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ADD-RES": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "TTY-C"
              ],
              "free_text": [
